I haven't been out to eat much lately so I've been slacking! Tonight we took a quick trip over to #epcot and found a little hidden gem in the back of #italy in the world showcase. We've been a million times and somehow we have always missed this!

We stepped out of a theme park and found ourselves in a quaint & cozy Italian wine cellar. Low lighting, great capacity control, clean and the wait staff was excellent. This is our new hideaway spot when we want to escape the crowds. They have small plates, paninis & desserts with wine & beer.

We ordered the #calimari which came with a delicious marinara & I discovered a new sparkling red wine that I'm obsessed with called Banfi Rosa Regale. I was told you can find it at Publix! From their description: "A delicate bouquet of rose petals and offers sensuous flavors of fresh raspberries and strawberries. Its effervescence is softer than that of champagne, yet it yields a persistent and delicate pink froth. " 

Go check it out! You'll be glad you did!
#epcotfoodandwinefestival
